The paper deals with the compression and acceleration of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves subspace clustering, which is a technique commonly used in unsupervised learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions experiments on different networks and tasks, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
